      "rationale": "NIH predictions compared against experimental measurements using both absolute error metrics and the relative hemolysis index (RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate). Mean absolute error of 38% acknowledged explicitly; however, RH ratio comparisons show consistent rank-ordering of operating points (Spearman rho = 0.91), supporting the COU objective of identifying worst-case conditions. Confidence in absolute NIH prediction is ~50% as documented in ValidationResult vr-hemolysis-index-comparison-001; confidence in worst-case rank identification is ~75%. Gradation 2 achieved against required Gradation 2 based on documented quantitative comparison with uncertainty bounds."
