      "rationale": "Primary QoI is NIH (normalized index of hemolysis) derived from Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model applied to Lagrangian particle tracking through the CFD velocity and shear stress fields. NIH is the FDA-recommended metric for computational hemolysis assessment and directly maps to the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Secondary QoI is pump pressure-head, which validates hydraulic fidelity. Confidence in QoI relevance is high (~85%); the power-law damage model is a simplification of complex red blood cell mechanics, a limitation explicitly documented."
