  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepts the CFD hemolysis model for the COU1 objective (identifying worst-case operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at MRL 2) with explicit acknowledgement of the following honestly-documented limitations: (1) Absolute NIH prediction confidence is approximately 50%, with a mean absolute error of 38% and 95% CI spanning ±52% of experimental values, primarily driven by power-law blood damage model exponent uncertainty and turbulence model sensitivity. (2) Mesh convergence confidence for hemolysis QoIs is approximately 50% due to shear stress peak sensitivity in blade-tip gap regions. (3) Validation was performed using bovine blood rather than human blood, introducing an estimated 15% viscosity uncertainty. Despite these explicitly-documented low-confidence findings, the decision to Accept is grounded in the following structured evidence: (a) The COU objective is comparative worst-case identification using RH < 1, not absolute NIH prediction. The Spearman rank correlation of 0.91 between predicted and measured operating-point NIH values demonstrates that the model reliably identifies the worst-case condition even when absolute accuracy is limited. (b) All 7 assessed credibility factors achieve their required levels for MRL 2. The 6 scoped-out factors are documented with explicit rationale per ASME V&V 40 Table 1 requirements for MRL 2. (c) The uncertainty quantification records (UQ-001 through UQ-003) are fully linked to their respective ValidationResults and transparently report confidence levels, coverage intervals, and dominant uncertainty sources. No uncertainty has been concealed or minimised. (d) The RH < 1 acceptance criterion provides a conservative safety margin that accommodates the documented ±52% uncertainty: even at the upper bound of the confidence interval, all 5 operating points yield RH < 0.85 relative to the predicate device. (e) The decision consequence is High and model influence is Medium; this MRL 2 assessment is augmented by physical bench testing confirming hemolysis results, consistent with the medium model influence designation. The team concludes that the model is fit for the specific comparative purpose of the COU at MRL 2, and that the low-confidence evidence has been documented with sufficient transparency and structural completeness to support a credible Accepted determination.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
